</p>
<p class="jp">
神保町の「トロワバグ」のアイスコーヒー。クリームとガムシロップ用の小さなカップが添えられている。
</p>]]></content><author><name>Daniel Sofer</name></author><category term="Tokyo" /><category term="Food" /><summary type="html"><![CDATA[Ice coffee at Café Trois Bagues in Tokyo's Jimbocho district, with little cups for cream and liquid sugar. 神保町の「トロワバグ」のアイスコーヒー。クリームとガムシロップ用の小さなカップが添えられている。]]></summary><media:thumbnail xmlns:media="http://search.yahoo.com/mrss/" url="https://hermosawavephotography.com/assets/images/2026/2606_A7R02045_edit.jpg" /><media:content medium="image" url="https://hermosawavephotography.com/assets/images/2026/2606_A7R02045_edit.jpg" xmlns:media="http://search.yahoo.com/mrss/" /></entry><entry><title type="html">Grand Torii &amp;amp; Keiryu Bridge・大鳥居と慶流橋</title><link href="https://hermosawavephotography.com/260531/" rel="alternate" type="text/html" title="Grand Torii &amp;amp; Keiryu Bridge・大鳥居と慶流橋" /><published>2026-05-31T00:00:00+09:00</published><updated>2026-05-31T00:00:00+09:00</updated><id>https://hermosawavephotography.com/heian-torii</id><content type="html" xml:base="https://hermosawavephotography.com/260531/"><![CDATA[<p class="en">
At the edge of the Lake Biwa Canal, looking at the Heian Jingu shrine's vermillion Grand Torii and Keiryu Bridge. In the distance is the Kyoto City KYOCERA Museum of Art.
</p>
<p class="jp">
琵琶湖疏水のほとりから、平安神社の朱色の大きな鳥居と慶流橋を眺めている。遠くには京都市立京セラ美術館が見える。
</p>]]></content><author><name>Daniel Sofer</name></author><category term="Higashiyama" /><category term="Shrines" /><category term="Rivers" /><summary type="html"><![CDATA[At the edge of the Lake Biwa Canal, looking at the Heian Jingu shrine's vermillion Grand Torii and Keiryu Bridge. In the distance is the Kyoto City KYOCERA Museum of Art. 琵琶湖疏水のほとりから、平安神社の朱色の大きな鳥居と慶流橋を眺めている。遠くには京都市立京セラ美術館が見える。]]></summary><media:thumbnail xmlns:media="http://search.yahoo.com/mrss/" url="https://hermosawavephotography.com/assets/images/2026/2605_IMG_3871.jpg" /><media:content medium="image" url="https://hermosawavephotography.com/assets/images/2026/2605_IMG_3871.jpg" xmlns:media="http://search.yahoo.com/mrss/" /></entry><entry><title type="html">Morning in the Grove・朝の竹林</title><link href="https://hermosawavephotography.com/260530/" rel="alternate" type="text/html" title="Morning in the Grove・朝の竹林" /><published>2026-05-30T00:00:00+09:00</published><updated>2026-05-30T00:00:00+09:00</updated><id>https://hermosawavephotography.com/chikurin</id><content type="html" xml:base="https://hermosawavephotography.com/260530/"><![CDATA[<p class="en">
Early morning sunlight on my walk through Arashiyama's Bamboo Grove.
</p>
<p class="jp">
嵐山の竹林を散歩しながら、早朝の陽光。
</p>]]></content><author><name>Daniel Sofer</name></author><category term="Arashiyama" /><category term="Morning" /><category term="Bamboo Grove" /><summary type="html"><![CDATA[Early morning sunlight on my walk through Arashiyama's Bamboo Grove. 嵐山の竹林を散歩しながら、早朝の陽光。]]></summary><media:thumbnail xmlns:media="http://search.yahoo.com/mrss/" url="https://hermosawavephotography.com/assets/images/2026/2605_DSC_2775.jpg" /><media:content medium="image" url="https://hermosawavephotography.com/assets/images/2026/2605_DSC_2775.jpg" xmlns:media="http://search.yahoo.com/mrss/" /></entry><entry><title type="html">Blue Kamogawa・青鴨川</title><link href="https://hermosawavephotography.com/260529/" rel="alternate" type="text/html" title="Blue Kamogawa・青鴨川" /><published>2026-05-29T00:00:00+09:00</published><updated>2026-05-29T00:00:00+09:00</updated><id>https://hermosawavephotography.com/bluehour</id><content type="html" xml:base="https://hermosawavephotography.com/260529/"><![CDATA[<p class="en">
Looking over the Kamogawa river and Sanjo Ohashi bridge at blue hour after sunset. The paper lanterns on the outdoor dining terraces <em>(kawayuka)</em> are all aglow.
</p>
<p class="jp">
日没後のブルーアワー、鴨川と三条大橋を眺める。川床の紙提灯がすべて灯っている。
</p>]]></content><author><name>Daniel Sofer</name></author><category term="Kyoto" /><category term="Bridges" /><category term="Kamo River" /><category term="Dusk" /><summary type="html"><![CDATA[Looking over the Kamogawa river and Sanjo Ohashi bridge at blue hour after sunset. The paper lanterns on the outdoor dining terraces (kawayuka) are all aglow. 日没後のブルーアワー、鴨川と三条大橋を眺める。川床の紙提灯がすべて灯っている。]]></summary><media:thumbnail xmlns:media="http://search.yahoo.com/mrss/" url="https://hermosawavephotography.com/assets/images/2026/2605_A7R02023_edit-2.jpg" /><media:content medium="image" url="https://hermosawavephotography.com/assets/images/2026/2605_A7R02023_edit-2.jpg" xmlns:media="http://search.yahoo.com/mrss/" /></entry><entry><title type="html">Nakanoshima Bridge・中ノ島橋</title><link href="https://hermosawavephotography.com/260528/" rel="alternate" type="text/html" title="Nakanoshima Bridge・中ノ島橋" /><published>2026-05-28T00:00:00+09:00</published><updated>2026-05-28T00:00:00+09:00</updated><id>https://hermosawavephotography.com/nakanoshimabridge</id><content type="html" xml:base="https://hermosawavephotography.com/260528/"><![CDATA[<p class="en">
The small Nakanoshima Bridge, connecting Nakanoshima Island with Arashiyama.
</p>
<p class="jp">
中ノ島と嵐山を結ぶ、小さな中ノ島橋だ。
</p>
<p class="en">🎞️ Fujifilm Velvia 50 Film</p>]]></content><author><name>Daniel Sofer</name></author><category term="Arashiyama" /><category term="Bridges" /><category term="Film" /><summary type="html"><![CDATA[The small Nakanoshima Bridge, connecting Nakanoshima Island with Arashiyama. 中ノ島と嵐山を結ぶ、小さな中ノ島橋だ。 🎞️ Fujifilm Velvia 50 Film]]></summary><media:thumbnail xmlns:media="http://search.yahoo.com/mrss/" url="https://hermosawavephotography.com/assets/images/2026/2605_DSC_2742_edit.jpg" /><media:content medium="image" url="https://hermosawavephotography.com/assets/images/2026/2605_DSC_2742_edit.jpg" xmlns:media="http://search.yahoo.com/mrss/" /></entry><entry><title type="html">Squares Building・ スクエアのビル</title><link href="https://hermosawavephotography.com/260526/" rel="alternate" type="text/html" title="Squares Building・ スクエアのビル" /><published>2026-05-26T00:00:00+09:00</published><updated>2026-05-26T00:00:00+09:00</updated><id>https://hermosawavephotography.com/squares</id><content type="html" xml:base="https://hermosawavephotography.com/260526/"><![CDATA[<p class="en">
This building in Shinsaibashi caught my eye.
</p>
<p class="jp">
心斎橋にあるこの建物が目に留まった。
</p>]]></content><author><name>Daniel Sofer</name></author><category term="Osaka" /><category term="Architecture" /><summary type="html"><![CDATA[This building in Shinsaibashi caught my eye. 心斎橋にあるこの建物が目に留まった。]]></summary><media:thumbnail xmlns:media="http://search.yahoo.com/mrss/" url="https://hermosawavephotography.com/assets/images/2026/2605_A7R01927_edit.jpg" /><media:content medium="image" url="https://hermosawavephotography.com/assets/images/2026/2605_A7R01927_edit.jpg" xmlns:media="http://search.yahoo.com/mrss/" /></entry><entry><title type="html">Bridge &amp;amp; Shrine・橋と神社</title><link href="https://hermosawavephotography.com/260525/" rel="alternate" type="text/html" title="Bridge &amp;amp; Shrine・橋と神社" /><published>2026-05-25T00:00:00+09:00</published><updated>2026-05-25T00:00:00+09:00</updated><id>https://hermosawavephotography.com/bridgeandshrine</id><content type="html" xml:base="https://hermosawavephotography.com/260525/"><![CDATA[<p class="en">
